title: Demand Deposits at Banks Due to Foreign Commercial Banks (DISCONTINUED)
notes: This series has been discontinued and will no longer be updated. Starting on February 23, 2021, the H.6 statistical release is now published at a monthly frequency and contains only monthly average data needed to construct the monetary aggregates, thereby eliminating the release of data on institutional money funds and memorandum items on U.S. government deposits and deposits due to foreign banks and foreign official institutions. For further information about the changes to the H.6 Statistical Release, see the announcements (https://www.federalreserve.gov/feeds/h6.html) provided by the source.

title: IRA and Keogh Accounts: Total
IRA and Keogh Accounts at Commercial Banks (DISCONTINUED)
notes: This series has been discontinued and will no longer be updated. It has been consolidated under the following series, which will continue to be updated: IRA (https://fred.stlouisfed.org/series/IRA).  Starting on February 23, 2021, the H.6 statistical release is now published at a monthly frequency and contains only monthly average data needed to construct the monetary aggregates. Components of the monetary aggregates are reported at a total industry level without a breakdown by banks and thrifts. For further information about the changes to the H.6 Statistical Release, see the announcements (https://www.federalreserve.gov/feeds/h6.html) provided by the source.
